    <section id="xhtml_dragdrop_actions">
      <title>XHTML Drag/Drop (or Copy/Paste) Actions</title>
      <p id="drag-and-drop-from-project-to-author-docbook4">Dragging a file from the <xref
          href="using-the-project-view.dita#using-the-project-view" format="dita"><uicontrol
            product="author editor">Project</uicontrol><uicontrol
            product="authorEclipse editorEclipse">Project Explorer</uicontrol> view</xref> and dropping it
        into an XHTML document that is edited in <uicontrol>Author</uicontrol> mode, creates a link
        to the dragged file (the <xmlelement>a</xmlelement> element with the <xmlatt>href</xmlatt>
        attribute) at the drop location. Copy and paste actions work the same.</p>
      <p>You can also drag images or media files from your system explorer or the <xref
          href="using-the-project-view.dita#using-the-project-view" format="dita"><uicontrol
            product="author editor">Project</uicontrol><uicontrol
            product="authorEclipse editorEclipse">Project Explorer</uicontrol> view</xref> and drop them
        into an XHTML document (or copy and paste). This will insert the appropriate element at the
        drop or paste location (for example, dropping/pasting an image will insert the
        <xmlelement>img</xmlelement> element with the <xmlatt>src</xmlatt> attribute).</p>
    </section>
